@node Features "Features"

   @{b}TRANSLATIONS@{ub}

   0 - English for French 
   1 - English for German 
   2 - English for Italian 
   3 - English for Portuguese 
   4 - English for Spanish 
   5 - French for English 
   6 - German for English 
   7 - Italian for English 
   8 - Spanish for English 
   9 - Portuguese for English 

   @{b}ARexx scripts interface integrations@{ub}

   * Fully integration with Amirc        (IRC client)
   * Fully integration with Aweb         (WWW Client)
   * Fully integration with IBrowser     (WWW Client)
   * Fully integration with Yam          (E-Mail Client)
   * Fully integration with Microdot II  (E-Mail Client)
   * Fully integration with Final Writer (Text Editor)
   * Fully integration with WordWorth    (Text Editor)

@endnode

@node HowItWorks "I wonder how it works..."

   @{u}How it works?@{uu}

   This program allows you  to  translate  texts  and  documents  in many
languages using a  powerfull server  available  on the internet, allowing
a good and fast translation, using  what  exists  of  more  modern  about
translation texts.

   @{b}FTrans Translator Servers supported@{ub}

   http://translator.go.com (no char limit!)
   http://babelfish.altavista.digital.com

   Amiga is only a Translation @{u}client@{uu}.

   @{b}Remember@{ub}: Its a online translation, you need it  connect  on  internet 
for success on translation.

@endnode

@node Req "What it needs?"

   @{u}Requirements@{uu}

   * An Amiga AGA, ECS or UAE emulator;
   * Workbench 2.0+;
   * 2 Megabytes memory (we recommend more);
   * libs:socket.library

   @{u}for use Freedom ARexx scripts you need@{uu}

   * libs:rexxtricks.library
   * libs:rexxsupport.library

@endnode

@node Usage "How to use it?"

   @{u}Usefull examples@{uu}

   Call help
   @{b}FTranslator HELP@{ub}

   Translates a sentence  (3 - English to Portuguese)
   @{b}FTranslator -T "This is a good program..." -D 3@{ub}

   Translate a text file (9 - Portuguese to English)
   @{b}FTranslator -F "ram:txtfile" -D 9@{ub}

   Translate a text with out display status messages
   @{b}FTranslator -T "this program is cool :)" -D 3 SILENCE@{ub}

   Translate a text with only translated output messages
   @{b}FTranslator -T "this program is cool :)" -D 3 SILENCEMAX@{ub}

   Translate a url and save output file on outputfile.html
   FTranslator -U "www.microsoft.com" -D 3 -O "Ram:outputfile.html"

   @{b}AREXX SCRIPTS INTERFACE EXAMPLES@{ub}

   @{u}Amirc@{uu}
   * Just select text on amirc window;
   * Press Amirc button with translation direction;
     It's open in the same windows your display with
     your translation of your text selected.

   @{u}AWeb@{uu}
   * Select text on home page;
   * Go to menu and select translation direction;
     It's open one request with your translation.

     @{b}Or@{ub}

   * Use option to translate current frame;
   * Aweb open a new window browser with all html translated.

     @{b}Or@{ub}

   * Use popup link to open selected url in a new translation
   window.

   @{u}IBrowser@{uu}
   * Select text on home page;
   * Go to menu and select translation direction;
     It's open multiview window with your translation.   

   @{u}Yam@{uu}
   * Select text
   * Go to menu and select translation direction;
     It's open the request or mail windows with your
     translation.

   @{u}WordWorth@{uu}
   * Select text
   * Go to menu and select translation option;
   * Select translation direction in request; 
     It's open other WordWorth window with your
     translation.
   
   @{u}FinalWriter@{uu}
   * Select text
   * Go to menu and select translation option;
     It's open other FinalWriter window with your
     translation.
   
@endnode

